Rezu Mezu <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=niemam>NiemaM</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#330000>(2/7/04 8:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=247.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mezz Aggro?</span><hr size=1> Ok, first off mez has a huge aggro, I mean you make a mob stand still and watch its buddy get killed. In pop I always kept boggle up so if I retained aggro after break that would most often make it go away. In LDoN however boggle seems very ineffective. For LdoN I use blur on break not boggle if I am getting beat on. That is what you can do to take far less smack down.<br>
<br>
The real issue here though is who is it that you group with. Any warr pally or sk can get aggro off you in a heartbeat if they know their stuff. I do agree that it can take warr a few more sec to get aggro over you but it doesnt flip flop like it can with sk or pally. Well I will exclude the formidable pallies from that statement, There are two pally whom I have grouped with that know that voodoo that they do soo well they can take aggro and keep it off you even if you were to chain tash sitting down between each cast.<br>
<br>
When a mob is mezzd the aggro list is absolutely most definitely NOT froze while mez. If you are only on mez and another ench tashes and a shammy slows that mob when it breaks its not coming for you. In fact, the very first mez spell we get with a likelyhood of blurring greater than 1% we dont get until level 54 that is GoK and that has a 30% chance of blur. Rapture, ancient eternal rapture and bliss are our three spells with the highest chance of a blur which is 40%. So we get a 40% chance that mob wont clober us as soon as is breaks.<br>
<br>
The key to avoiding mez aggro deaths is to use your defensive spells bv, gv, boggle, blur and most importantly root. Above all make sure you group with those whom you know can take aggro. If you are in a pick up group keep root up or you will tank. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=braellarth>Braellarth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#330000>(2/8/04 12:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=247.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mezz Aggro?</span><hr size=1> It takes 4 successful taunts <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">IF</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> you have attack off to take agro.<br>
<br>
Easy way to test is get a friend to agro a mob, turn his attack off and you try and taunt the creature off him, if you have your attack off it takes four successful taunts until he turns on you each and every time.<br>
<br>
The same is for mesed mobs, with attack off it will take four successful taunts.<br>
<br>
Which makes taunting mesed mobs before breaking mes pointless imho, unless you can generate agro via spells or have left over agro from before the mes spell hit, another option is just root the creature then let the melee break it, then they can attack and get agro from taunt in the normal way.<br>
<br>
Brae<br>
FVie<br>
